message.content:
cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.PF

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing Internet traffic and estimating the quality of an Internet connection. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also fall under this category as it discusses the use of NetFlow protocol to collect data, which is a security feature in Cisco routers. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may also be categorized under this as it uses queuing theory to compare expressions for backbone traffic. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may also fall under this category as it deals with analyzing network traffic and determining the working area and overloading point of the network. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper may also be categorized under this as it proposes a methodology for plotting a curve that shows the dependence of utilization of a link on a number of active flows in it, which can be used to determine the moment for upgrading the backbone.
